{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 05:12:41.814096", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nSummary of network health\n- Overall state: Major outage of data-plane connectivity across the fabric.\n- Scope: All host-to-host communication is failing, including within the same leaf (same L2 subnet), due to lack of ARP resolution. This is consistent with an SDN control-plane failure and Open vSwitch (OVS) fail_mode behavior.\n- Control plane: All OVS switches (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) are not connected to the controller; they are in fail_mode secure with no flows installed.\n\nKey symptoms observed\n- Intra-leaf connectivity fails:\n  - host_1_1 -> host_1_2: 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable.”\n  - host_2_1 -> host_2_2: 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable.”\n- Cross-leaf connectivity also fails:\n  - host_1_1 -> host_2_1: 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable.”\n- ARP resolution failing:\n  - On host_1_1: ip neigh shows “10.0.0.2 dev eth0 FAILED” and “10.0.0.9 dev eth0 FAILED.”\n- Hosts’ NICs are up and configured (10.0.0.0/24), but RX packets remain 0 while TX shows a few frames (likely ARP requests not returned).\n\nControl-plane and switch state\n- All OVS bridges are configured with a controller at tcp:20.0.0.100:6633 and fail_mode: secure.\n- Controller connection status on all three switches:\n  - is_connected: false\n  - status: last_error=\"Connection refused\", state=BACKOFF\n- No flows installed:\n  - ovs-ofctl dump-flows leaf_1 returns empty.\n- Physical ports appear up at 10Gb/full duplex per ovs-ofctl show and dump-ports-desc; only the LOCAL internal port is down as expected.\n\nManagement-plane reachability\n- From leaf_1, ping to the controller at 20.0.0.100 succeeds (low latency, 0% loss).\n- This confirms basic IP reachability to the controller host, but the OpenFlow TCP connection is being refused (i.e., service not listening on 6633 or using a different port).\n\nAnomaly detection\n- Abnormal: Complete failure of L2 broadcast/ARP and host connectivity across the fabric.\n- Abnormal: All switches report “Connection refused” to the controller target with fail_mode secure and no flows, causing all traffic to be dropped.\n\nFault localization\n- The OVS data plane is behaving as designed in secure fail mode (no controller, no forwarding).\n- The issue is centralized at the SDN controller endpoint (20.0.0.100:6633):\n  - Switches can reach the controller host (ICMP OK).\n  - TCP connection to the configured OpenFlow port (6633) is refused.\n  - This indicates the controller service is not accepting connections on 6633 or is not running, misconfigured, or listening on a different port.\n\nProbable root cause\n- SDN controller service unavailability or port mismatch at 20.0.0.100:6633, resulting in all switches falling back to fail_mode secure with no flows, which blocks ARP and all host traffic.\n- Not a physical link fault: switch ports are up and counters show link is established.\n- Not a host configuration fault: hosts have correct IPs and interfaces are up; ARP failures point to lack of L2 flooding/forwarding by the leaf switches due to missing control-plane programming.\n\nImpact assessment\n- Fabric-wide data connectivity outage:\n  - Intra-leaf L2 switching disabled.\n  - Inter-leaf forwarding disabled.\n  - All hosts in 10.0.0.0/24 effectively isolated.\n\nSupporting evidence (selected)\n- Pings:\n  - host_1_1 -> host_1_2: “Destination Host Unreachable,” 100% loss.\n  - host_2_1 -> host_2_2: “Destination Host Unreachable,” 100% loss.\n  - host_1_1 -> host_2_1: “Destination Host Unreachable,” 100% loss.\n- ARP:\n  - host_1_1: ip neigh shows FAILED for 10.0.0.2 and 10.0.0.9.\n- Switch/controller:\n  - leaf_1: Controller target tcp:20.0.0.100:6633, fail_mode: secure, is_connected: false, status: last_error=\"Connection refused\".\n  - Same status on leaf_2 and spine_1.\n  - ovs-ofctl dump-flows leaf_1: no flows.\n- Management-plane:\n  - leaf_1 -> 20.0.0.100: ICMP reachable.\n\nConclusion\n- The network is experiencing a control-plane outage at the SDN controller endpoint (OpenFlow service refusing connections on 6633). With OVS fail_mode set to secure and no flows installed, the entire data-plane is nonfunctional, evidenced by ARP failures and host unreachable errors even within a single leaf.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 21299, "output_tokens": 2625, "total_tokens": 23924, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 17152}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1536}}}
